Police have arrested one of the suspected ringleaders in the Zandspruit vigilante attack that took place in Johannesburg last month. Given Mabodze was arrested on Friday after being on the run for weeks. Eight men died after being beaten and set alight by community members. Six men were previously arrested and have appeared in court. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu report. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police have arrested one of the suspected ringleaders in the Zandspruit vigilante attack that took place in Johannesburg last month. Given Mabodze was arrested on Friday after being on the run for weeks. Eight men died after being beaten and set alight by community members. READ: Vigilante Attack | 6 Zandspruit accused in court Six men were previously arrested and have appeared in court. Watch the video above for more details on this story.